This is a basic note taking web application.

There are six main files needed to run this application.

1. index.html. This file contains basic HTML functionality such as buttons and other page elements, and running src files.
2. edit.html. This file contains HTML functionality specifically for editing notes, which will open a new page in the application.
3. note-app.js. This file runs functions which have been refactored in the notes-functions.js file.
4. notes-functions.js. This file contains the vital functions needing for running the application, including taking notes, saving notes to localStorage, and DOM rendering.
5. notes-edit.js. This file contains basic functions used for editing notes.
6. uuidv4.js. This file contains a function that is used to give each note a unqiue reference ID, which is used for a variety of purposes.
